obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (5315)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406&sectionId=5315&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Smugglers and Foreign`
  line `Exchange Manipulators (Forfeiture of Property) Act, 1976.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India except the State of Jammu and Kashmir*.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall be deemed to have come into force on the 5th day of November, 1975.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `*. Vide Notification No. S.O. 3912 (E), dated 30th October, 2019, this Act is made applicable to the Union territory of Jammu and`
  line `Kashmir and the Union territory of Ladakh.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (5316)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Application.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes `1. Section 2A, omitted by Act 28 of 2016, s. 226 (w.e.f. 1-6-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406&sectionId=5316&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) The provisions of this Act shall apply only to the persons specified in`
  line `sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(2) The persons referred to in sub-section (1) are the following, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) every person--`
  line
  line `(i) who has been convicted under the Sea Customs Act, 1878 (8 of 1878), or the Customs`
  line `Act, 1962 (52 of 1962), of an offence in relation to goods of a value exceeding one lakh of`
  line `rupees; or`
  line
  line `(ii) who has been convicted under the Foreign Exchange Regulation Act, 1947 (7 of 1947), or`
  line `the Foreign Exchange Regulation Act, 1973 (46 of 1973), of an offence, the amount or value`
  line `involved in which exceeds one lakh of rupees; or`
  line
  line `(iii) who having been convicted under the Sea Customs Act, 1878 (8 of 1878), or the`
  line `Customs Act, 1962 (52 of 1962), has been convicted subsequently under either of those Acts; or`
  line
  line `(iv) who having been convicted under the Foreign Exchange Regulation`
  line `Act, 1947 (7 of 1947), or the Foreign Exchange Regulation Act, 1973 (46 of 1973), has been`
  line `convicted subsequently under either of those Acts;`
  line
  line `(b) every person in respect of whom an order of detention has been made under the Conservation`
  line `of Foreign Exchange and Prevention of Smuggling Activities Act, 1974 (52 of 1974):`
  line
  line `Provided that--`
  line
  line `(i) such order of detention, being an order to which the provisions of section 9 or section 12A`
  line `of the said Act do not apply, has not been revoked on the report of the Advisory Board under`
  line `section 8 of the said Act or before the receipt of the report of the Advisory Board or before`
  line `making a reference to the Advisory Board; or`
  line
  line `(ii) such order of detention, being an order to which the provisions of section 9 of the said Act`
  line `apply, has not been revoked before the expiry of the time for, or on the basis of, the review under sub-section (3) of section 9, or on the report of the Advisory Board under section 8, read with`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 9, of the said Act; or`
  line
  line `(iii) such order of detention, being an order to which the provision of section 12A of the said`
  line `Act apply, has not been revoked before the expiry of the time for, or on the basis of, the first`
  line `review under sub-section (3) of that section, or on the basis of the report of the Advisory Board`
  line `under section 8, read with sub-section (6) of section 12A, of that Act; or`
  line
  line `(iv) such order of detention has not been set aside by a court of competent jurisdiction;`
  line
  line `(c) every person who is a relative of a person referred to in clause (a) or clause (b);`
  line
  line `(d) every associate of a person referred to in clause (a) or clause (b);`
  line
  line `(e) any holder (hereafter in this clause referred to as the present holder) of any property which`
  line `was at any time previously held by a person referred to in clause (a) or clause (b) unless the present`
  line `holder or, as the case may be, any one who held such property after such person and before the`
  line `present holder, is or was a transferee in good faith for adequate consideration.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.--For the purposes of sub-clause (i) of clause (a), the value of any goods in relation to`
  line `which a person has been convicted of an offence shall be the wholesale price of the goods in the ordinary`
  line `course of trade in India as on the date of the commission of the offence.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.--For the purposes of clause (c), "relative", in relation to a person, means--`
  line
  line `(i) spouse of the person;`
  line
  line `(ii) brother or sister of the person;`
  line
  line `(iii) brother or sister of the spouse of the person;`
  line
  line `(iv) any lineal ascendant or descendant of the person;`
  line
  line `(v) any lineal ascendant or descendant of the spouse of the person;`
  line
  line `(vi) spouse of a person referred to in clause (ii), clause (iii) clause (iv) or clause (v);`
  line
  line `(vii) any lineal descendant of a person referred to in clause (ii) or clause (iii).`
  line
  line `Explanation 3@/i--@.For the purposes of clause (d), "associate", in relation to a person, means--`
  line
  line `(i) any individual who had been or is residing in the residential premises (including outhouses) of`
  line `such person;`
  line
  line `(ii) any individual who had been or is managing the affairs or keeping the accounts of such`
  line person;
  line
  line `(iii) any association of persons, body of individuals, partnership firm, or private company within`
  line `the meaning of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), of which such person had been or is a member,`
  line `partner or director;--`
  line
  line `(iv) any individual who had been or is a member, partner or director of an association of persons,`
  line `body of individuals, partnership firm or private company referred to in clause (iii) at any time when`
  line `such person had been or is a member, partner or director of such association, body, partnership firm`
  line `or private company;`
  line
  line `(v) any person who had been or is managing the affairs, or keeping the accounts, of an association`
  line `of persons, body of individuals, partnership firm or private company referred to in clause (iii);`
  line
  line `(vi) the trustee of any trust, where,--`
  line
  line `(a) the trust has been created by such person; or`
  line
  line `(b) the value of the assets contributed by such person (including the value of the assets, if`
  line `any, contributed by him earlier) to the trust amounts, on the date on which the contribution is`
  line `made, to not less than twenty per cent. of the value of the assets of the trust on that date;`
  line
  line `(vii) where the competent authority, for reasons to be recorded in writing, considers that any`
  line `properties of such person are held on his behalf by any other person, such other person.`
  line
  line `Explanation 4.-- For the avoidance of doubt, it is hereby provided that the question whether any`
  line `person is a person to whom the provisions of this Act apply may be determined with reference to any`
  line `facts, circumstances or events (including any conviction or detention) which occurred or took place`
  line `before the commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line ^1
  line `* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_2_a:
  sectionId (5317)
  sectionNo 2A
  orderNo 3
  title `Act not to apply to certain persons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 2 of 1989, s. 22 (w.e.f. 29-5-1989).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406&sectionId=5317&sectionno=2A&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406
obj_root_law_sections_2_a_content:
  string
  line `^1On and from the commencement of the provisions of`
  line `Chapter VA of the Narcotic Drugs and Psychotropic Substances Act, 1985 (61 of 1985), the provisions of`
  line `this Act shall not apply to persons in relation to whom any order, or proceeding, may be made or taken`
  line `under that Chapter.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (5318)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 4
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. The words "for Forfeited Property", omitted by s. 226, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-6-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406&sectionId=5318&sectionno=3&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,`
  line
  line `(a) "Appellate Tribunal" means the Appellate ^1`
  line `*** Tribunal for Forfeited Property constituted under`
  line `section 12;`
  line
  line `(b) "competent authority" means an officer of the Central Government authorised by it under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 5 to perform the functions of a competent authority under this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) "illegally acquired property", in relation to any person to whom this Act applies, means--`
  line
  line `(i) any property acquired by such person, whether before or after the commencement of this`
  line `Act, wholly or partly out of or by means of any income, earnings or assets derived or obtained`
  line `from or attributable to any activity prohibited by or under any law for the time being in force`
  line `relating to any matter in respect of which Parliament has power to make laws; or`
  line
  line `(ii) any property acquired by such person, whether before or after the commencement of this`
  line `Act, wholly or partly out of or by means of any income, earning or assets in respect of which any`
  line `such law has been contravened; or`
  line
  line `(iii) any property acquired by such person, whether before or after the commencement of this`
  line `Act, wholly or partly out of or by means of any income, earnings or assets the source of which`
  line `cannot be proved and which cannot be shown to be attributable to any act or thing done in respect`
  line `of any matter in relation to which Parliament has no power to make laws; or`
  line
  line `(iv) any property acquired by such person, whether before or after the commencement of this`
  line `Act, for a consideration, or by any means, wholly or partly traceable to any property referred to in`
  line `sub-clauses (i) to (iii) or the income or earnings from such property;`
  line
  line `and includes--`
  line
  line `(A) any property held by such person which would have been, in relation to any previous`
  line `holder thereof, illegally acquired property under this clause if such previous holder had not`
  line `ceased to hold it, unless such person or any other person who held the property at any time after`
  line `such previous holder or, where there are two or more such previous holders, the last of such`
  line `previous holders is or was a transferee in good faith for adequate consideration;`
  line
  line `(B) any property acquired by such person, whether before or after the commencement of this`
  line `Act, for a consideration, or by any means, wholly or partly traceable to any property falling under`
  line `item (A), or the income or earnings therefrom;`
  line
  line `(d) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(e) "property" includes any interest in property, movable or immovable;`
  line
  line `(f) "trust" includes any other legal obligation.`
  line
  line `(2) Any reference in this Act to any law which is not in force in any area shall, in relation to that area,`
  line `be construed as a reference to the corresponding law, if any, in force in that area.`
  line
  line `(3) Any reference in this Act to any officer or authority shall, in relation to any area in which there is`
  line `no officer or authority with the same designation, be construed as a reference to such officer or authority`
  line `as may be specified by the Central Government by notification in the Official Gazette.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (5319)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 5
  title `Prohibition of holding illegally acquired property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406&sectionId=5319&sectionno=4&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) As from the commencement of this`
  line `Act, it shall not be lawful for any person to whom this Act applies to hold any illegally acquired property`
  line `either by himself or through any other person on his behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any person holds any illegally acquired property in contravention of the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (1), such property shall be liable to be forfeited to the Central Government in accordance with`
  line `the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (5320)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 6
  title `Competent authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406&sectionId=5320&sectionno=5&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by order published in the Official`
  line `Gazette, authorise as many officers of the Central Government (not below the rank of a Joint Secretary to`
  line `the Government), as it thinks fit, to perform the functions of the competent authority under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The competent authorities shall perform their functions in respect of such persons or classes of`
  line `persons as the Central Government may, by order, direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (5321)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 7
  title `Notice of forfeiture.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406&sectionId=5321&sectionno=6&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, having regard to the value of the properties held by any person to`
  line `whom this act applies, either by himself or through any other person on his behalf, his known sources of`
  line `income, earnings or assets, and any other information or material available to it as a result of action taken`
  line `under section 18 or otherwise, the competent authority has reason to believe (the reasons for such belief to`
  line `be recorded in writing) that all or any of such properties are illegally acquired properties, it may serve a`
  line `notice upon such person (hereinafter referred to as the person affected) calling upon him within such time`
  line `as may be specified in the notice, which shall not be ordinarily less than thirty days, to indicate the`
  line `sources of his income, earnings or assets, out of which or by means of which he has acquired such`
  line `property, the evidence on which he relies and other relevant information and particulars, and to show`
  line `cause why all or any of such properties, as the case may be, should not be declared to be illegally acquired`
  line `properties and forfeited to the Central Government under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a notice under sub-section (1) to any person specifies any property as being held on behalf`
  line `of such person by any other person, a copy of the notice shall also be served upon such other person.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (5322)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 8
  title `Forfeiture of property in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406&sectionId=5322&sectionno=7&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The competent authority may, after considering the`
  line `explanation, if any, to the show-cause notice issued under section 6, and the materials available before it`
  line `and after giving to the person affected (and in a case where the person affected holds any property`
  line `specified in the notice through any other person, to such other person also) a reasonable opportunity of`
  line `being heard, by order, record a finding whether all or any of the properties in question are illegally`
  line `acquired properties.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the competent authority is satisfied that some of the properties referred to in the`
  line `show-cause notice are illegally acquired properties but is not able to identity specifically such properties,`
  line `then, it shall be lawful for the competent authority to specify the properties which, to the best of its`
  line `judgment, are illegally acquired properties and record a finding accordingly under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) Where the competent authority records a finding under this section to the effect that any property`
  line `is illegally acquired property, it shall declare that such property shall, subject to the provisions of this Act,`
  line `stand forfeited to the Central Government free from all encumbrances.`
  line
  line `(4) Where any shares in a company stand forfeited to the Central Government under this Act, then,`
  line `the company shall, notwithstanding anything contained in the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), or the`
  line `articles of association of the company, forthwith register the Central Government as the transferee of such`
  line shares.
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (5323)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 9
  title `Burden of proof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406&sectionId=5323&sectionno=8&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `In any proceedings under this Act, the burden of proving that any property`
  line `specified in the notice served under section 6 is not illegally acquired property shall be on the person`
  line affected.
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (5324)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 10
  title `Fine in lieu of forfeiture.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406&sectionId=5324&sectionno=9&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the competent authority makes a declaration that any`
  line `property stands forfeited to the Central Government under section 7 and it is a case where the source of`
  line `only a part, being less than one-half, of the income, earnings or assets with which such property was`
  line `acquired has not been proved to the satisfaction of the competent authority, it shall make an order giving`
  line `an option to the person affected to pay, in lieu of forfeiture, a fine equal to one and one-fifth times the`
  line `value of such part.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, the value of any part of income, earnings or`
  line `assets, with which any property has been acquired, shall be,--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of any part of income or earnings, the amount of such part of income or earnings;`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of any part of assets, the proportionate part of the full value of the consideration for`
  line `the acquisition of such assets.`
  line
  line `(2) Before making an order imposing a fine under sub-section (1), the person affected shall be given a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the person affected pays the fine due under sub-section (1), within such time as may be`
  line `allowed in that behalf, the competent authority may, by order, revoke the declaration of forfeiture under`
  line `section 7 and thereupon such property shall stand released.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (5325)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 11
  title `Procedure in relation to certain trust properties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406&sectionId=5325&sectionno=10&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `In the case of any person referred to in`
  line `clause (vi) of Explanation 3 to sub-section (2) of section 2, if the competent authority, on the basis of the`
  line `information and materials available to it, has reason to believe (the reasons for such belief to be recorded`
  line `in writing) that any property held in trust is illegally acquired property, it may serve a notice upon the`
  line `author of the trust or, as the case may be, the contributor of the assets out of or by means of which such`
  line `property was acquired by the trust and the trustees, calling upon them within such time as may be`
  line `specified in the notice which shall not ordinarily be less than thirty days, to explain the source of the`
  line `money or other assets out of or by means of which such property was acquired or, as the case may be, the`
  line `source of the money or other assets which were contributed to the trust for acquiring such property and`
  line `thereupon such notice shall be deemed to be a notice served under section 6 and all the other provisions of`
  line `this Act shall apply accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section "illegally acquired property", in relation to any`
  line `property held in trust, includes--`
  line
  line `(i) any property which if it had continued to be held by the author of the trust or the contributor of`
  line `such property to the trust would have been illegally acquired property in relation to such author or`
  line contributor;
  line
  line `(ii) any property acquired by the trust out of any contributions made by any person which would`
  line `have been illegally acquired property in relation to such person had such person acquired such`
  line `property out of such contributions.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (5326)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 12
  title `Certain transfers to be null and void.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406&sectionId=5326&sectionno=11&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `Where after the issue of a notice under section 6 or`
  line `under section 10, any property referred to in the said notice is transferred by any mode whatsoever such`
  line `transfer shall, for the purposes of the proceedings under this Act, be ignored and if such property is`
  line `subsequently forfeited to the Central Government under section 7, then, the transfer of such property shall`
  line `be deemed to be null and void.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (5327)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 13
  title `Constitution of Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406&sectionId=5327&sectionno=12&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, constitute an Appellate Tribunal ^1`
  line `*** consisting of a Chairman and such number of other members (being`
  line `officers of the Central Government not below the rank of a Joint Secretary to the Government) as the Central`
  line `Government thinks fit, to be appointed by the Government for ^2`
  line `[hearing appeals the orders made--`
  line
  line `(a) under section 7, sub-section (1) of section 9 or section 10;`
  line
  line `(b) under section 68F, section 68-I, sub-section (1) of section 68K or section 68L, of the Narcotic Drugs`
  line `and Psychotropic Substances Act, 1985 (61 of 1985);`
  line
  line `(c) by the Adjudicating Authority or any other authority under the Prevention of Money-laundering`
  line `Act, 2002, (15 of 2003);]`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairman of the Appellate Tribunal shall be a person who is or has been ^3`
  line `*** a Judge of the`
  line `Supreme Court or of a High Court.`
  line
  line `(3) The terms and conditions of service of the Chairman and other members shall be such as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(4) Any person aggrieved by an order of the competent authority made under section 7, sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 9 or section 10, may, within forty-five days from the date on which the order is served on him, prefer`
  line `an appeal to the Appellate Tribunal:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Appellate Tribunal may entertain any appeal after the said period of forty-five days, but`
  line `not after sixty days, from the date aforesaid if it is satisfied that the appellant was prevented by sufficient cause`
  line `from filing the appeal in time.`
  line
  line `(5) On receipt of an appeal under sub-section (4), the Appellate Tribunal may, after giving an opportunity`
  line `to the appellant to be heard, if he so desires, and after making such further enquiry as it deems fit, confirm,`
  line `modify or set aside the order appealed against.`
  line
  line `(6) The powers and functions of the Appellate Tribunal may be exercised and discharged by Benches`
  line `consisting of three members and constituted by the Chairman of the Appellate Tribunal.`
  line
  line ^4
  line `[(6A) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (6), where the Chairman considers it necessary`
  line `so to do for the expeditious disposal of appeals under this section, he may constitute a ^5`
  line `[Bench with one or two`
  line `members] and a Bench so constituted may exercise and discharge the powers and functions of the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the members of a Bench so constituted differ on any point or points, they shall state the`
  line `point or points on which they differ and refer the same to a third member (to be specified by the Chairman) for`
  line `hearing on such point or points and such point or points shall be decided according to the opinion of that`
  line member.]
  line
  line ^6
  line `[(6B) In the event of the occurrence of any vacancy in the office of the Chairman by reason of his death,`
  line `resignation or otherwise, the senior-most member, shall act as the Chairman until the date on which a new`
  line `Chairman, appointed in accordance with the provisions of this Act to fill such vacancy, enters upon his office.`
  line
  line `(6C) When the Chairman is unable to discharge his functions owing to absence, illness or any other cause,`
  line `the senior-most member shall discharge the functions of the Chairman until the date on which the Chairman`
  line `resumes his duties.]`
  line
  line `(7) The Appellate Tribunal may regulate its own procedure.`
  line
  line ^4
  line `[(8) On application to the Appellate Tribunal and on payment of the prescribed fee, the Tribunal may`
  line `allow a party to any appeal or any person authorised in this behalf by such party to inspect at any time during`
  line `office hours, any relevant records and registers of the Tribunal and obtain a certified copy of any part thereof.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "to be called the Appellate Tribunal for Forfeited Property" omitted by Act 28 of 2016 s. 226 (w.e.f. 1-6-2016).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 226, ibid., for "hearing appeals against the orders made under section 7, sub-section (1) of section 9 or section 10"`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-6-2016).`
  line
  line `3. The words "or is qualified to be" omitted by s. 226, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-6-2016).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 55 of 1980, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-7-1981).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 226, for "Bench of two members" (w.e.f. 1-6-2016)`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by s. 226, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-6-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_12_a:
  sectionId (57703)
  sectionNo 12A
  orderNo 14
  title `Qualifications, terms and conditions of service of Chairperson, and Member.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406&sectionId=57703&sectionno=12A&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406
obj_root_law_sections_12_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[12A. Qualifications, terms and conditions of service of Chairperson, and Member.--`
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, the qualifications, appointment, term of office, salaries`
  line `and allowances, resignation, removal and the other terms and conditions of service of the Chairperson and`
  line `other members of the Appellate Tribunal appointed after the commencement of ^2[the Tribunals Reforms`
  line `Act, 2021, shall be governed by the provisions of Chapter II of the said Act]:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Chairperson and other members appointed before the commencement of Part XIV`
  line `of Chapter VI of the Finance Act, 2017 (7 of 2017), shall continue to be governed by the provisions of`
  line `this Act, and the rules made thereunder as if the provisions of section 184 of the Finance Act, 2017 had`
  line `not come into force.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 164 (w.e.f. 26-5-2017).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 33 of 2021, s. 14, for Part XIV of Chapter VI of the Finance Act, 2017 (7 of 2017), shall be governed by the provisions of section 184 of that Act (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (5328)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 15
  title `Notice or order not to be invalid for error in description.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406&sectionId=5328&sectionno=13&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `No notice issued or served, no`
  line `declaration made, and no order passed, under this Act shall be deemed to be invalid by reason of any error`
  line `in the description of the property or person mentioned therein if such property or person is identifiable`
  line `from the description so mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (5329)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 16
  title `Bar of jurisdiction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406&sectionId=5329&sectionno=14&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `No order passed or declaration made under this Act shall be appealable`
  line `except as provided therein and no civil court shall have jurisdiction in respect of any matter which the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal or any competent authority is empowered by or under this Act to determine, and no`
  line `injunction shall be granted by any court or other authority in respect of any action taken or to be taken in`
  line `pursuance of any power conferred by or under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (5330)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 17
  title `Competent authority and Appellate Tribunal to have powers of civil court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406&sectionId=5330&sectionno=15&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `The competent`
  line `authority and the Appellate Tribunal shall have all the powers of a civil court while trying a suit under the`
  line `Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of documents;`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence or affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) requisitioning any public record or copy thereof from any court or office;`
  line
  line `(e) issuing commissions for examination of witnesses or documents;`
  line
  line `(f) any other matter which may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (5331)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 18
  title `Information to competent authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406&sectionId=5331&sectionno=16&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other`
  line `law, the competent authority shall have power to require any officer or authority of the Central`
  line `Government or a State Government or a local authority to furnish information in relation to such persons,`
  line `points or matters as in the opinion of the competent authority will be useful for, or relevant to, the`
  line `purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Any officer of the Income-tax Department, the Customs Department or the Central Excise`
  line `Department or any officer of enforcement appointed under the Foreign Exchange Regulation`
  line `Act, 1973 (46 of 1973), may furnish sou motu any information available with him to the competent`
  line `authority if in the opinion of the officer such information will be useful to the competent authority for the`
  line `purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (5332)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 19
  title `Certain officers to assist competent authority and Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406&sectionId=5332&sectionno=17&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of`
  line `any proceedings under this Act, the following officers are hereby empowered and required to assist the`
  line `competent authority and the Appellate Tribunal, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) officers of the Customs Department;`
  line
  line `(b) officers of the Central Excise Department;`
  line
  line `(c) officers of the Income-tax Department;`
  line
  line `(d) officers of enforcement appointed under the Foreign Exchange Regulation`
  line `Act, 1973 (46 of 1973);`
  line
  line `(e) officers of police;`
  line
  line `(f) such other officers of the Central or State Government as are specified by the Central`
  line `Government in this behalf by notification in the Official Gazette.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (5333)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 20
  title `Power of competent authority to require certain officers to exercise certain powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406&sectionId=5333&sectionno=18&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) For`
  line `the purposes of any proceedings under this Act or the initiation of any such proceedings, the competent`
  line `authority shall have power to cause to be conducted any inquiry, investigation or survey in respect of any`
  line `person, place, property, assets, documents, books of account or any other relevant matters.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes referred to in sub-section (1), the competent authority may, having regard to the`
  line `nature of the inquiry, investigation or survey, require an officer of the Income-tax Department to conduct`
  line `or cause to be conducted such inquiry, investigation or survey.`
  line
  line `(3) Any officer of the Income-tax Department who is conducting or is causing to be conducted any`
  line `inquiry, investigation or survey required to be conducted under sub-section (2), may, for the purpose of`
  line `such inquiry, investigation or survey, exercise any power (including the power to authorise the exercise of`
  line `any power) which may be exercised by him for any purpose under the Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961),`
  line `and the provisions of the said Act shall, so far as may be, apply accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (5334)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 21
  title `Power to take possession.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406&sectionId=5334&sectionno=19&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any property has been declared to be forfeited to the`
  line `Central Government under this Act, or where the person affected has failed to pay the fine due under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 9 within the time allowed therefor under sub-section (3) of that section, the`
  line `competent authority may order the person affected as well as any other person who may be in possession`
  line `of the property to surrender or deliver possession thereof to the competent authority or to any person duly`
  line `authorised by it in this behalf within thirty days of the service of the order.`
  line
  line `(2) If any person refuses or fails to comply with an order made under sub-section (1), the competent`
  line `authority may take possession of the property and may for that purpose use such force as may be`
  line necessary.
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (2), the competent authority may, for the`
  line `purpose of taking possession of any property referred to in sub-section (1), requisition the service of any`
  line `police officer to assist the competent authority and it shall be the duty of such officer to comply with such`
  line requisition.
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (5335)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 22
  title `Rectification of mistakes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406&sectionId=5335&sectionno=20&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `With a view to rectifying any mistakes apparent from record, the`
  line `competent authority or the Appellate Tribunal, as the case may be, may amend any order made by it`
  line `within a period of one year from the date of the order:`
  line
  line `Provided that if any such amendment is likely to affect any person prejudicially, it shall not be made`
  line `without giving to such person a reasonable opportunity of being heard.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (5336)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 23
  title `Findings under other laws not conclusive for proceedings under this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406&sectionId=5336&sectionno=21&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `No finding of any`
  line `officer or authority under any other law shall be conclusive for the purposes of any proceeding under this`
  line Act.
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (5337)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 24
  title `Service of notices and orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406&sectionId=5337&sectionno=22&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `Any notice or order issued or made under this Act shall be`
  line served--
  line
  line `(a) by tendering the notice or order or sending it by registered post to the person for whom it is`
  line `intended or to his agent;`
  line
  line `(b) if the notice or order cannot be served in the manner provided in clause (a), by affixing it on a`
  line `conspicuous place in the property in relation to which the notice or order is issued or made, or on`
  line `some conspicuous part of the premises in which the person for whom it is intended is known to have`
  line `last resided or carried on business or personally worked for gain.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (5338)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 25
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406&sectionId=5338&sectionno=23&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other proceeding shall lie`
  line `against the Central Government or any officer of the Central or State Government for anything which is`
  line `done, or intended to be done, in good faith, in pursuance of this Act or the rules made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (5339)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 26
  title `Act to have overriding effect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406&sectionId=5339&sectionno=24&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall have effect notwithstanding`
  line `anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (5340)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 27
  title `Provisions of the Act not to apply to certain properties held in trust.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406&sectionId=5340&sectionno=25&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `Nothing contained in`
  line `this Act shall apply in relation to any property held by a trust or an institution created or established`
  line `wholly for public, religious or charitable purposes if--`
  line
  line `(i) such property has been so held by such trust or institution from a date prior to the`
  line `commencement of this Act; or`
  line
  line `(ii) such property is wholly traceable to any property held by such trust or institution prior to the`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (5341)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 28
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 55 of 1980, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-7-1981).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406&sectionId=5341&sectionno=26&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the terms and conditions of service of the Chairman and other members of the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal under sub-section (3) of section 12;`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(aa) the fees which shall be paid for the inspection of the records and registers of the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal or for obtaining a certified copy of any part thereof under sub-section (8) of section 12;]`
  line
  line `(b) the powers of a civil court that may be exercised by the competent authority and the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal under clause (f) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(c) any other matter which has to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House`
  line `of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one`
  line `session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule, or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified from or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (5342)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 29
  title `Repeal and saving.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406&sectionId=5342&sectionno=27&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00005_197613_1517807318406
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Smugglers and Foreign Exchange Manipulators (Forfeiture of`
  line `Property) Ordinance, 1975 (20 of 1975), is hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal, anything done or any action taken under the Ordinance so repealed`
  line `shall be deemed to have been done or taken under the corresponding provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
